title: Guest goes overboard on P&O cruise: It was 'worst thing I've seen on a cruise,' says passenger
summary: A passenger says a rogue wave or a shaky ship isn't to blame for an incident that took place on a P&O cruise liner this week, in which a passenger went overboard near the Pacific archipelago of New Caledonia. The Pacific Dawn was in the middle of a week-long cruise of the Pacific islands when, at approximately 4 p.m. on Thursday, a crew member spotted a female passenger go over the side of the ship, the Australian Broadcasting Corporation reported. A spokesman for the cruise line told the outlet that a “person overboard” response was sent to the bridge crew, who immediately reversed course to search for the passenger. “[It was] by far the worst thing I've seen happen on a cruise,” said a witness, identified as Ms. An by the Australian Associated Press (AAP).

summary: Special counsel Robert Mueller has majority support in a new ABC News/Washington Post poll for extending his investigation into both Donald Trump’s business dealings and the alleged payment of hush money to women who say they’ve had affairs with the president in the past. Support extends to half of conservatives and more than four in 10 Republicans.
